  "text": "In terms of conserving waterfalls and maintaining their aesthetic appeal for tourists, tourism managers need to be mindful of the impacts of high visitation at waterfall sites. Tourism impacts include vandalism and graffiti, soil erosion, damage to vegetation, degradation of facilities and over-development [CITATION_1] . In terms of Mauritian waterfalls, this once again raises the question of conducting regular site assessments, as well as the need for planning for tourism pressure and avoiding over-exploitation of the site.",
